1
00:00:07,416 --> 00:00:11,250
♪

2
00:00:18,875 --> 00:00:21,041
[man singing in Japanese]

3
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,875
[indistinct chatter]

4
00:01:43,958 --> 00:01:45,375
[SAIKI]
Four o'clock.

5
00:01:45,458 --> 00:01:47,583
If I leave now,
I'll be home with time to spare.

6
00:01:47,666 --> 00:01:49,416
Which is good,
because there's a TV show

7
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:51,833
I absolutely cannot miss
airing at 5.

8
00:01:51,916 --> 00:01:54,791
[TV ANNOUNCER]
Healthy Warriors. Specializer.

9
00:01:56,583 --> 00:01:58,791
[SAIKI] Don't think anime
is just for kids.

10
00:01:58,875 --> 00:02:00,375
This is mature animation

11
00:02:00,458 --> 00:02:03,166
for a discriminating viewer
like myself.

12
00:02:03,250 --> 00:02:07,166
Uh-oh. Kaidou's up ahead.
Better double back.

13
00:02:07,250 --> 00:02:09,708
I can't find Saiki anywhere.
Huh.

14
00:02:09,791 --> 00:02:12,208
I found a really cool
abandoned building

15
00:02:12,291 --> 00:02:15,041
that I've turned into
my Jet Black Wings lair.

16
00:02:15,125 --> 00:02:17,750
He'll love seeing what I've done
with the place.

17
00:02:17,833 --> 00:02:20,625
My own hideout.
I mean, a super-secret base.

18
00:02:20,708 --> 00:02:22,000
[SAIKI]
I'd rather not.

19
00:02:23,333 --> 00:02:25,375
Saiki, where are you, bro?

20
00:02:25,458 --> 00:02:27,166
Since he helped me
the other day,

21
00:02:27,250 --> 00:02:28,416
I thought I'd repay
the favor

22
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,125
by inviting him
to the gym.

23
00:02:30,208 --> 00:02:31,375
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
Muscle.

24
00:02:31,458 --> 00:02:32,916
[HAIRO]
We can spot each other.

25
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,708
[SAIKI]
Yeah, pass.

26
00:02:34,791 --> 00:02:36,541
If you wanna repay my favor,
Hairo,

27
00:02:36,625 --> 00:02:38,708
you can start
by leaving me alone.

28
00:02:38,791 --> 00:02:40,916
[TERUHASHI]
Where is Kunio Saiki?

29
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,250
It's not like I really care
about him or anything,

30
00:02:43,333 --> 00:02:46,291
but the teacher said that I had
to bring him this form.

31
00:02:46,375 --> 00:02:48,500
Although it could be fun
to ask him out to tea,

32
00:02:48,583 --> 00:02:50,458
just to watch him get
all nervous and flip out.

33
00:02:50,541 --> 00:02:53,375
He won't be able to think
I'm an illusion if I corner him.

34
00:02:53,458 --> 00:02:55,166
[SAIKI]
Yeah, whatever.

35
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:57,125
Why is today's episode
so important?

36
00:02:57,208 --> 00:02:58,916
Because it's
the season finale--

37
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,833
Hey, buddy! Wanna go get some
ramen with your best friend?

38
00:03:01,916 --> 00:03:02,875
[SAIKI]
Leave me alone.

39
00:03:02,958 --> 00:03:04,166
Huh? Hm?

40
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:05,625
♪

41
00:03:05,708 --> 00:03:08,083
[SAIKI]
I'm trapped at school.

42
00:03:08,166 --> 00:03:11,541
Every route's blocked by someone
I want nothing to do with.

43
00:03:11,625 --> 00:03:14,416
I could teleport,
but then I wouldn't get to stop

44
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:16,750
at the locker and take off
my school shoes.

45
00:03:16,833 --> 00:03:18,375
Hm. Well, I only need
30 minutes

46
00:03:18,458 --> 00:03:19,791
to get home.
I'll wait them out.

47
00:03:21,416 --> 00:03:24,333
No one is leaving.

48
00:03:24,416 --> 00:03:26,291
Hairo's at the front gate.

49
00:03:26,375 --> 00:03:29,541
[HAIRO] I won't leave
till I get to thank him.

50
00:03:29,625 --> 00:03:31,375
[SAIKI]
Kaidou's at the shoe locker.

51
00:03:31,458 --> 00:03:33,083
When Saiki's taking off
his shoes,

52
00:03:33,166 --> 00:03:36,416
I'll jump out and scare him
as a test of his reflexes.

53
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:37,666
[SAIKI]
As for her.

54
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:38,666
Excuse me.
Hm?

55
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:40,708
Oh, wow! Hey, Teruhashi.

56
00:03:40,791 --> 00:03:42,333
Can you please help me
find Saiki?

57
00:03:42,416 --> 00:03:43,875
I've been looking,
but there's just

58
00:03:43,958 --> 00:03:45,875
too much ground to cover
for a girl like me.

59
00:03:45,958 --> 00:03:48,125
[TAKAHASHI]
Yes, yes, of course I'll help!

60
00:03:48,208 --> 00:03:51,541
[SAIKI] Teruhashi and her
worker drones are everywhere.

61
00:03:51,625 --> 00:03:53,125
Now I'm really screwed.

62
00:03:53,208 --> 00:03:55,041
Leaving is suddenly
near impossible.

63
00:03:55,125 --> 00:03:57,166
If you're wondering why
I don't record this show,

64
00:03:57,250 --> 00:03:58,958
it's because the moment
it's over,

65
00:03:59,041 --> 00:04:01,541
spoilers will flood into my head
from people who have seen it.

66
00:04:01,625 --> 00:04:02,833
[MAN 1]
Who knew it was a dream?

67
00:04:02,916 --> 00:04:04,541
[WOMAN 1] I called
that guy dying.

68
00:04:04,625 --> 00:04:06,833
[MAN 2] Too many montages.
[SAIKI] It can't be helped.

69
00:04:06,916 --> 00:04:09,000
My only choice
is to become invisible.

70
00:04:09,083 --> 00:04:11,291
This only makes it
so people can't see me.

71
00:04:11,375 --> 00:04:13,791
I'm still here, physically,
able to interact with things.

72
00:04:13,875 --> 00:04:15,750
But there are some
pretty big drawbacks.

73
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:17,416
I can only do it
for 10 minutes,

74
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,333
and if anyone touches
me while I'm like this,

75
00:04:19,416 --> 00:04:21,083
I'll become visible
immediately.

76
00:04:21,166 --> 00:04:22,791
I've got to handle this
carefully.

77
00:04:22,875 --> 00:04:24,166
[toilet flushes]

78
00:04:24,250 --> 00:04:26,250
Ah, that hit the spot.

79
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:29,166
Better get back
to finding my buddy.

80
00:04:29,250 --> 00:04:30,958
[SAIKI]
Ah. That was almost game over.

81
00:04:31,041 --> 00:04:33,375
But knowing Nendou's location
is a big help.

82
00:04:33,458 --> 00:04:36,041
His unpredictability is the
biggest threat to this power.

83
00:04:36,125 --> 00:04:39,375
Now I just go in the other
direction and lay low.

84
00:04:39,458 --> 00:04:41,541
Ugh, where in the hell
is that damn Saiki?

85
00:04:41,625 --> 00:04:43,083
[SAIKI]
Right here.

86
00:04:43,166 --> 00:04:44,875
For the sake of everyone
watching at home,

87
00:04:44,958 --> 00:04:47,125
I'll make myself
visible to you.

88
00:04:47,208 --> 00:04:51,333
How cute, the locker where
Kaidou's been hiding.

89
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:53,333
[Kaidou screams]
What's wrong, Kaidou?

90
00:04:53,416 --> 00:04:55,750
[KAIDOU] Ghost just lifted up
the locker I was hiding in.

91
00:04:55,833 --> 00:04:57,791
No, wait. It wasn't a ghost,
it was Dark Reunion.

92
00:04:57,875 --> 00:05:00,333
[TERUHASHI] Slow down, nothing
you're saying makes sense.

93
00:05:00,416 --> 00:05:01,625
[SAIKI]
Now's my chance.

94
00:05:01,708 --> 00:05:03,666
Hold on, I'll save you!

95
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:05,625
What happened?
I heard a scream.

96
00:05:05,708 --> 00:05:08,250
It's Dark Reunion.
They found my hiding spot.

97
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:10,125
Oh. Okay. Yeah.
Oh, of course.

98
00:05:10,208 --> 00:05:11,750
[SAIKI]
Nendou's on the other side

99
00:05:11,833 --> 00:05:13,666
of the building,
and the rest are right here.

100
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:15,291
Now to just
switch my shoes and--

101
00:05:15,375 --> 00:05:18,291
[TORITSUKA]
Finally heading home, Saiki?

102
00:05:18,375 --> 00:05:19,583
I'll walk with you, pal.

103
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:22,041
[SAIKI]
You idiot.

104
00:05:22,125 --> 00:05:24,041
[ALL]
Ah! There he is!

105
00:05:24,125 --> 00:05:25,333
Uh...

106
00:05:25,416 --> 00:05:27,083
Saiki, I need to repay
your favor.

107
00:05:27,166 --> 00:05:28,916
Our teacher asked me
to give these to you.

108
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,375
I have a lair now.

109
00:05:30,458 --> 00:05:32,583
[ALL]
You're not busy, are you?

110
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:33,583
Uh...

111
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:35,208
Ah, Teruhashi.

112
00:05:35,291 --> 00:05:36,833
[SAIKI]
So it's not just ghosts.

113
00:05:36,916 --> 00:05:38,625
He can see anything
invisible.

114
00:05:38,708 --> 00:05:41,875
[TAKAHASHI]
Saiki? Hello?

115
00:05:41,958 --> 00:05:45,125
♪

116
00:05:46,958 --> 00:05:48,750
[SAIKI]
Sports Day.

117
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:50,916
[HAIRO] Listen up, guys.
Today's about one thing:

118
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,291
us being number one!
[ALL] Let's do it!

119
00:05:53,375 --> 00:05:55,791
[SAIKI] I was all set to skip
school today, but...

120
00:05:55,875 --> 00:05:57,375
But you can't miss
Sports Day.

121
00:05:57,458 --> 00:06:00,083
Yeah, I bought a camcorder
just for the occasion.

122
00:06:00,166 --> 00:06:01,875
[SAIKI]
...they guilted me into coming.

123
00:06:01,958 --> 00:06:04,166
That's right, look over
this way. Just like that.

124
00:06:04,250 --> 00:06:05,500
Oh, crap, the battery died.

125
00:06:05,583 --> 00:06:06,958
[KURUMI] Oh, no.
[SAIKI] Go home.

126
00:06:07,041 --> 00:06:08,791
Class three, go!

127
00:06:08,875 --> 00:06:10,958
[SAIKI] Boy, those "yeahs"
are getting annoying.

128
00:06:11,041 --> 00:06:14,416
Sports Day is so stupid. Heh.
My skills are best used...

129
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:16,000
[SAIKI]
Hey, for the first time ever,

130
00:06:16,083 --> 00:06:17,833
Kaidou and I
agree on something.

131
00:06:17,916 --> 00:06:20,000
You're just saying that
'cause you suck at sports.

132
00:06:20,083 --> 00:06:22,166
[KAIDOU] Shut up!
[SAIKI] Wow, Nendou's headband

133
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:23,958
seems completely at home.

134
00:06:24,041 --> 00:06:26,583
Oh, right, it looks exactly
like the grooves in his hair.

135
00:06:26,666 --> 00:06:29,541
Yo, Saiki, hey.
[SAIKI] Oh, great.

136
00:06:29,625 --> 00:06:31,666
You pumped?
[SAIKI] The opposite of pumped.

137
00:06:31,750 --> 00:06:33,458
[HAIRO]
And Nendou, you're a fit guy.

138
00:06:33,541 --> 00:06:35,500
I expect big things
out there from you too.

139
00:06:35,583 --> 00:06:37,500
That's right.
You're not beating me this time.

140
00:06:37,583 --> 00:06:39,000
[SAIKI]
We're all on the same team.

141
00:06:39,083 --> 00:06:40,291
[HAIRO]
And Kaidou, my man.

142
00:06:40,375 --> 00:06:42,166
Just do whatever it is
you can do.

143
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:44,000
I'm sure you're gonna try
really hard.

144
00:06:44,083 --> 00:06:46,416
[KAIDOU] What's that mean?
[HAIRO] Don't fight with me.

145
00:06:46,500 --> 00:06:48,750
Fight with our competition.
They look tough this year.

146
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:50,958
First, Class One.
[SAIKI] Their symbol's a circle.

147
00:06:51,041 --> 00:06:53,375
[HAIRO] Every student in this
class is an intellectual.

148
00:06:53,458 --> 00:06:54,958
That's right!
[ALL] Yeah!

149
00:06:55,041 --> 00:06:57,125
[HAIRO] Class 2...
[SAIKI] Their symbol's a plus.

150
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:59,083
[HAIRO] Everyone in this class
is an athlete.

151
00:06:59,166 --> 00:07:01,041
[OOSHIMA] Class Two's gonna
curb-stomp you.

152
00:07:01,125 --> 00:07:03,333
[HAIRO] Class Four.
[SAIKI] Their symbol's a square.

153
00:07:03,416 --> 00:07:05,333
[HAIRO] More intellectuals,
led by Tanihara,

154
00:07:05,416 --> 00:07:06,458
who aced his midterms.

155
00:07:06,541 --> 00:07:07,791
We compete for
immortal glory.

156
00:07:07,875 --> 00:07:09,333
[SAIKI]
They'd rather be reading.

157
00:07:09,416 --> 00:07:11,333
[HAIRO] Class Five.
[SAIKI] They got the star.

158
00:07:11,416 --> 00:07:13,125
[HAIRO] Intellectuals
who wear glasses.

159
00:07:13,208 --> 00:07:14,708
They match
our hair and face types.

160
00:07:14,791 --> 00:07:16,750
[SAIKI] Is "intellectual"
your word of the day?

161
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:18,250
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
Our first event:

162
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:19,541
boys' hundred-meter dash.

163
00:07:19,625 --> 00:07:21,125
[SAIKI]
Great. I'm gonna have to run.

164
00:07:21,208 --> 00:07:22,708
Make them eat your dust, Kuu.

165
00:07:22,791 --> 00:07:24,958
I'm recording you, son,
to a tape called "my heart."

166
00:07:25,041 --> 00:07:27,791
You can do it, Saiki.
Win it for Class Three.

167
00:07:27,875 --> 00:07:29,791
[SAIKI]
I don't care about winning,

168
00:07:29,875 --> 00:07:33,458
because I don't want
to draw attention to myself.

169
00:07:33,541 --> 00:07:36,458
I'm in second place right now.
That's a little too conspicuous.

170
00:07:36,541 --> 00:07:37,916
I'll just fall back
into the pack.

171
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,708
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
That's the finish line.

172
00:07:39,791 --> 00:07:41,500
[SAIKI] Perfect.
Saiki. Holy crap, dude,

173
00:07:41,583 --> 00:07:42,750
you got third.

174
00:07:42,833 --> 00:07:44,458
[SAIKI]
Why is everyone so excited?

175
00:07:44,541 --> 00:07:46,833
All the other racers are on
the track-and-field team.

176
00:07:46,916 --> 00:07:48,916
The fourth-place guy
has a school sprint record.

177
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:51,375
[BOY] You should join track.
[SAIKI] I wish I knew before.

178
00:07:51,458 --> 00:07:54,541
Not bad, though I'm certain
I could smoke you one-on-one.

179
00:07:54,625 --> 00:07:56,791
Wait, that guy's running?
[SAIKI] Kaidou's up next?

180
00:07:56,875 --> 00:07:58,750
[MAN] On your marks.
[KAIDOU] I am the wind.

181
00:07:58,833 --> 00:08:00,500
I am the gale!

182
00:08:01,666 --> 00:08:02,958
[laughs]

183
00:08:03,041 --> 00:08:04,541
You need to go back
to running school.

184
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:06,375
We wound up tying
for fifth place.

185
00:08:06,458 --> 00:08:08,375
We gotta get a win on the board
in the next event.

186
00:08:08,458 --> 00:08:10,166
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
...Three-legged race.

187
00:08:10,250 --> 00:08:11,750
Ooh, it's time for me
to go to work.

188
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:13,500
[SAIKI] No, it's not.
[SAWAKITA] I'm up.

189
00:08:13,583 --> 00:08:15,500
I'm running in the three-legged
race, not you.

190
00:08:15,583 --> 00:08:17,916
[SAIKI] And who are you?
[SAWAKITA] My name is Sawakita.

191
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,833
But you don't have
to bother remembering it.

192
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:21,541
I'm just here to play
a supporting role.

193
00:08:21,625 --> 00:08:22,916
[SAIKI]
Now he's narrating?

194
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,583
[SAWAKITA]
From my grades to my looks,

195
00:08:24,666 --> 00:08:26,000
everything about me
is average.

196
00:08:26,083 --> 00:08:27,541
I was born average.

197
00:08:27,625 --> 00:08:29,833
But then, winning a single
rock-paper-scissors game

198
00:08:29,916 --> 00:08:31,416
brought a ray of hope
into my life.

199
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:33,625
I'm running the three-legged
race with Teruhashi.

200
00:08:33,708 --> 00:08:36,083
It's a memory I can cherish
for the rest of my average life.

201
00:08:36,166 --> 00:08:37,750
[SAIKI]
You're especially dramatic.

202
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:39,375
Try your best, Sawakita.

203
00:08:39,458 --> 00:08:41,666
From grades to looks,
everything about me is average.

204
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:43,708
But winning a single
rock-paper-scissors game

205
00:08:43,791 --> 00:08:45,166
brought a ray of hope
into my life.

206
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:46,750
I'm running the race
with Teruhashi.

207
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:48,875
It's a memory I can cherish for
the rest of my life.

208
00:08:48,958 --> 00:08:51,041
I bet that's what he's thinking.
[SAIKI] Amazing.

209
00:08:51,125 --> 00:08:52,750
She got it.
Certain you're not psychic?

210
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:55,000
[TERUHASHI] I hope he's not
so focused on me he loses.

211
00:08:55,083 --> 00:08:56,791
Let's win this together.
[SAWAKITA] Yes.

212
00:08:56,875 --> 00:08:59,208
[TERUHASHI] As sweet as I am,
I'm also very competitive.

213
00:08:59,291 --> 00:09:01,083
If we win this,
we should celebrate.

214
00:09:01,166 --> 00:09:02,333
Alone. Together.

215
00:09:02,416 --> 00:09:04,666
[MAN]
On your marks. Set.

216
00:09:04,750 --> 00:09:07,375
[screams]

217
00:09:07,458 --> 00:09:11,166
[BOY] Hey, this was supposed
to be the three-legged race.

218
00:09:11,250 --> 00:09:14,333
[SAIKI] I'm so honored to have
witnessed your cherished memory.

219
00:09:14,416 --> 00:09:17,291
Yeah. Let's keep that momentum
going, guys.

220
00:09:17,375 --> 00:09:19,791
A scavenger hunt race?
I wonder which one of us

221
00:09:19,875 --> 00:09:21,291
is gonna do that.
[SAIKI] You are.

222
00:09:21,375 --> 00:09:22,291
Oh, yeah, it's my turn.

223
00:09:22,375 --> 00:09:23,541
Come on, Nendou.

224
00:09:23,625 --> 00:09:24,916
[KAIDOU] Lose, lose, lose.

225
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,625
[NENDOU]
Nendou is hot out of the gates.

226
00:09:26,708 --> 00:09:28,166
He's coming home.

227
00:09:28,250 --> 00:09:31,083
[SAIKI]
You didn't win yet, Nendou.

228
00:09:31,166 --> 00:09:33,250
[MALE ANNOUNCER] Now go find
what's on that paper.

229
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:34,500
That's right. Ah...

230
00:09:34,583 --> 00:09:36,041
All right,
he's figured it out.

231
00:09:36,125 --> 00:09:38,666
Must be over here.
[NENDOU] Here, let me have this.

232
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:39,666
Yeah, sure.

233
00:09:39,750 --> 00:09:40,833
No, not the racket. This.

234
00:09:40,916 --> 00:09:42,041
Thanks.

235
00:09:43,625 --> 00:09:44,791
[all gasp]

236
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:46,875
[ALL]
Saiki!

237
00:09:47,916 --> 00:09:51,250
[man sings in Japanese]

238
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:55,458
♪

239
00:09:57,041 --> 00:09:59,625
[KAIDOU]
Saiki, wake up.

240
00:09:59,708 --> 00:10:01,083
Kaidou, what happened?

241
00:10:01,166 --> 00:10:02,708
I don't know.
He just fell over.

242
00:10:02,791 --> 00:10:04,750
Wake up, Saiki.

243
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:06,708
[HAIRO]
No, wait, don't move him.

244
00:10:06,791 --> 00:10:08,291
[both gasp]

245
00:10:08,375 --> 00:10:09,791
--[HAIRO] Saiki?
--[KAIDOU] Saiki!.

246
00:10:09,875 --> 00:10:11,416
[NENDOU]
Oh, my bad.

247
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:13,833
[KAIDOU] There's something
wrong with his face.

248
00:10:13,916 --> 00:10:16,000
[WASA CREWMAN]
Status report, ISS.

249
00:10:16,083 --> 00:10:18,916
We're in trouble. The main power
system suddenly went down.

250
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,083
I've never seen anything
like this happen before.

251
00:10:21,166 --> 00:10:23,958
[WASA CREWMAN] What?
[MAN] Oh, no. Oh, my God!

252
00:10:24,041 --> 00:10:25,583
[alarm blares]

253
00:10:25,666 --> 00:10:27,166
No. It can't be.

254
00:10:27,250 --> 00:10:29,416
Get me the President
of the United States now.

255
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:31,833
[TRIBE CHIEF]
What do you mean, elder?

256
00:10:31,916 --> 00:10:33,375
I have had a vision
of the future,

257
00:10:33,458 --> 00:10:36,125
and the world will soon
come to an end.

258
00:10:37,625 --> 00:10:39,791
Are you feeling okay?
We were worried.

259
00:10:39,875 --> 00:10:42,291
You fainted when Nendou took
that thing out of your head,

260
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:43,500
so I tried to put it back.

261
00:10:43,583 --> 00:10:44,958
[SAIKI]
He pulled out my antenna?

262
00:10:45,041 --> 00:10:46,583
[WASA CREWMAN]
Is it back?

263
00:10:46,666 --> 00:10:48,708
The power came back
when I smacked the generator.

264
00:10:48,791 --> 00:10:49,958
[WASA CREWMAN]
Did what?

265
00:10:50,041 --> 00:10:51,458
Now all of our readings
are normal.

266
00:10:51,541 --> 00:10:53,458
[MAN] Director,
the president's on the line.

267
00:10:53,541 --> 00:10:55,458
Whoops. Sorry, kids.
False alarm.

268
00:10:55,541 --> 00:10:56,750
[BOTH]
What?

269
00:10:56,833 --> 00:10:58,291
[sighs]

270
00:10:58,375 --> 00:11:00,333
[SAIKI] Since the antenna
was only out for a bit,

271
00:11:00,416 --> 00:11:02,000
the doomsday scenario
didn't happen.

272
00:11:02,083 --> 00:11:04,041
--I almost lost my buddy.
--[SAIKI] The real bad news

273
00:11:04,125 --> 00:11:05,708
is that Nendou's the one
who did it.

274
00:11:05,791 --> 00:11:10,333
That makes him a danger.
I'll have to eliminate him.

275
00:11:10,416 --> 00:11:12,333
Nothing I could have done
about that one, guys.

276
00:11:12,416 --> 00:11:14,166
I mean, when your best buddy
passes out,

277
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:16,250
there are more important
things than Sports Day.

278
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:17,625
We'll get the next one.

279
00:11:17,708 --> 00:11:19,458
[TAKAHASHI] He passed out
because of you!

280
00:11:19,541 --> 00:11:22,083
[MALE ANNOUNCER] And that's
the end of our morning events.

281
00:11:22,166 --> 00:11:24,333
Well, pal, sounds like
it's time for food.

282
00:11:24,416 --> 00:11:25,541
Hey, where'd Saiki go?

283
00:11:25,625 --> 00:11:27,291
Saiki?

284
00:11:27,375 --> 00:11:28,625
Where are you?

285
00:11:28,708 --> 00:11:29,750
Tres bien!

286
00:11:32,833 --> 00:11:34,458
[SAIKI]
I'm not feeling so hot.

287
00:11:34,541 --> 00:11:36,500
It doesn't matter if it was
only out for a second,

288
00:11:36,583 --> 00:11:38,208
it's causing me
all sorts of problems.

289
00:11:38,291 --> 00:11:41,083
The antenna Nendou removed
is a kind of control device.

290
00:11:41,166 --> 00:11:43,041
The psychic superpowers
I was born with

291
00:11:43,125 --> 00:11:46,125
have only gotten stronger
as I've grown older.

292
00:11:46,208 --> 00:11:49,708
By fifth grade, I could already
lift a high-rise with my mind.

293
00:11:49,791 --> 00:11:52,125
I probably could've blown up
the moon if I wanted to,

294
00:11:52,208 --> 00:11:55,291
but all that psychic power
is that much harder to control.

295
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:59,750
Blowing up the house in my sleep
is a best-case scenario.

296
00:11:59,833 --> 00:12:02,208
What's most worrisome
is my mind-control power.

297
00:12:02,291 --> 00:12:05,208
I could accidentally destroy
the world with a single thought.

298
00:12:05,291 --> 00:12:08,000
It would make explosions
seem like a day at the beach.

299
00:12:08,083 --> 00:12:11,083
So to restrain those powers,
I wear these on my head.

300
00:12:11,166 --> 00:12:14,125
But it can only restrain
my ability, not stop it.

301
00:12:14,208 --> 00:12:16,708
Underneath, it's always
growing in strength.

302
00:12:16,791 --> 00:12:20,208
Once these antennae come off,
I have no idea what will happen.

303
00:12:20,291 --> 00:12:22,125
My body's not
listening to me.

304
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:23,875
At this rate,
I could really hurt someone

305
00:12:23,958 --> 00:12:25,625
if I keep participating
in Sports Day.

306
00:12:25,708 --> 00:12:27,000
I've got to go home.

307
00:12:27,083 --> 00:12:28,958
[NENDOU] Saiki!
You playing hide-and-seek?

308
00:12:29,041 --> 00:12:31,083
[SAIKI] Crap.
Well, that's my cue. Teleport.

309
00:12:31,166 --> 00:12:32,416
Hello? Huh?

310
00:12:32,500 --> 00:12:33,916
Doing some private
stretching?

311
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,166
[SAIKI]
It's not working.

312
00:12:35,250 --> 00:12:36,416
My powers are messed up.

313
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:37,666
[NENDOU]
Hey, you all right?

314
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:39,708
Maybe you should
go home early.

315
00:12:39,791 --> 00:12:41,541
[SAIKI]
That might be my opening.

316
00:12:41,625 --> 00:12:42,666
Sorry to hear you're sick.

317
00:12:42,750 --> 00:12:43,833
You need help getting home?

318
00:12:43,916 --> 00:12:45,041
[GIRL] How are you feeling?

319
00:12:45,125 --> 00:12:46,791
[BOY] Drink lots of liquids.

320
00:12:46,875 --> 00:12:50,125
Yeah, we're gonna win the
afternoon events in your honor.

321
00:12:50,208 --> 00:12:51,166
[SAIKI]
Don't say that.

322
00:12:51,250 --> 00:12:52,541
[HAIRO]
No way we're losing now.

323
00:12:52,625 --> 00:12:54,666
--Let's win it all for Saiki.
--[ALL] Yeah!

324
00:12:54,750 --> 00:12:56,375
[HAIRO] Never forget
what he did for us!

325
00:12:56,458 --> 00:12:58,125
[SAIKI]
Now I can't leave.

326
00:12:58,208 --> 00:13:00,458
[MALE ANNOUNCER] Let's hear it
for the Amazing Chouno.

327
00:13:00,541 --> 00:13:01,541
No one watched us today.

328
00:13:01,625 --> 00:13:02,750
We've been on a losing streak

329
00:13:02,833 --> 00:13:03,916
ever since that TV special.

330
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,583
[MALE ANNOUNCER] ...tug-of-war.

331
00:13:05,666 --> 00:13:07,791
All right, guys and gals,
these are the team events.

332
00:13:07,875 --> 00:13:09,333
While we may be
at the bottom...

333
00:13:09,416 --> 00:13:11,541
[SAIKI] He didn't do any
individual events, did he?

334
00:13:11,625 --> 00:13:12,875
...that's about to change!

335
00:13:12,958 --> 00:13:14,541
Pull, pull, pull!

336
00:13:14,625 --> 00:13:16,125
Clench your teeth
and pull that rope!

337
00:13:16,208 --> 00:13:18,750
Squat and lean back!
Squat and lean back!

338
00:13:18,833 --> 00:13:20,375
[SAIKI]
Stop talking and pull.

339
00:13:20,458 --> 00:13:22,291
I don't even like gym
when I'm healthy,

340
00:13:22,375 --> 00:13:25,166
and now I've got to do
a tug-of-war like this?

341
00:13:25,250 --> 00:13:26,458
Oh.

342
00:13:26,541 --> 00:13:28,041
[TAKAHASHI]
It suddenly got light.

343
00:13:28,125 --> 00:13:29,791
--[SAIKI] Gotta stall.
--[TAKAHASHI] Whoa!

344
00:13:29,875 --> 00:13:31,000
Now it's heavy again!

345
00:13:31,083 --> 00:13:32,625
[SAIKI]
Why did it snap so easily?

346
00:13:32,708 --> 00:13:34,708
Oh, well, I bet I can fix it
before anyone notices.

347
00:13:34,791 --> 00:13:36,583
All right, this shouldn't
be too hard.

348
00:13:36,666 --> 00:13:40,166
Oh, crap, again?
The friction tore my gloves.

349
00:13:40,250 --> 00:13:42,416
I don't know what'll happen if I
use psychometry now.

350
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:43,500
[all yelling]

351
00:13:43,583 --> 00:13:45,833
Oops.
[bodies crashing]

352
00:13:45,916 --> 00:13:48,833
[JUDGE]
Uh...Class Three wins.

353
00:13:48,916 --> 00:13:51,125
All right, we won!
[people cheer]

354
00:13:51,208 --> 00:13:54,208
[SAIKI] I knew I should have
skipped school today.

355
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:56,958
Sports Day is the worst.

356
00:13:57,041 --> 00:13:59,750
♪

357
00:14:02,041 --> 00:14:04,166
[BOY]
Class Three is crazy.

358
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:06,500
We're not crazy, we're just
the kings of Sports Day.

359
00:14:06,583 --> 00:14:08,375
Battling real people's
kind of fun.

360
00:14:08,458 --> 00:14:10,041
I don't remember
eating lunch.

361
00:14:10,125 --> 00:14:12,416
It's torn where I was
holding it? Am I that strong?

362
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:14,583
[BOY] I've never seen them
so cocky.

363
00:14:14,666 --> 00:14:16,791
[SAIKI] They're not cocky
so much as stupid.

364
00:14:16,875 --> 00:14:18,375
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
After tug-of-war,

365
00:14:18,458 --> 00:14:20,166
Class Three moves up
to fourth place.

366
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:22,333
[SAIKI]
Still two more events.

367
00:14:22,416 --> 00:14:24,500
Even if you did, you would still
be doing terribly.

368
00:14:24,583 --> 00:14:26,333
Class Two is gonna beat you
hands down.

369
00:14:26,416 --> 00:14:27,791
[SAIKI]
Eh, couldn't care less.

370
00:14:27,875 --> 00:14:29,541
Hey, you respect us
for being number one!

371
00:14:29,625 --> 00:14:30,958
[SAIKI]
Again, I don't care.

372
00:14:31,041 --> 00:14:32,375
I came in last
in the race,

373
00:14:32,458 --> 00:14:34,208
but it was worth it.
[SAIKI] I can't believe

374
00:14:34,291 --> 00:14:36,041
you're bragging
about how that went down.

375
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:37,833
Just don't hold a grudge
when we win.

376
00:14:37,916 --> 00:14:40,125
[SAIKI] For the last time,
I don't care about who wins.

377
00:14:40,208 --> 00:14:42,208
Sorry, groper,
but Class Three's winning this.

378
00:14:42,291 --> 00:14:44,708
In fact, if we lose to you,
I'll buzz-cut my hair.

379
00:14:44,791 --> 00:14:46,333
--There's no way.
--[HAIRO] Yes, way.

380
00:14:46,416 --> 00:14:47,916
That's how much I believe in us.

381
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:50,000
[SAIKI] Please don't.
[BOY] Yeah, if we lose....

382
00:14:50,083 --> 00:14:51,958
--[ALL] We'll get a buzz cut.
--[SAIKI] Slow down.

383
00:14:52,041 --> 00:14:53,208
You can count me in too.

384
00:14:53,291 --> 00:14:54,875
There's no way
I'll let us lose.

385
00:14:54,958 --> 00:14:56,916
[SAIKI] Where are you getting
this confidence?

386
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,625
I want in on this
buzz cut bet too.

387
00:14:58,708 --> 00:15:00,791
[SAIKI] In your case,
a buzz cut's an improvement.

388
00:15:00,875 --> 00:15:02,541
I know what's next.

389
00:15:02,625 --> 00:15:05,208
We all share in the glory,
or every guy in Class Three

390
00:15:05,291 --> 00:15:06,500
will get a buzz cut!

391
00:15:06,583 --> 00:15:07,958
[SAIKI]
We are gonna look so dumb.

392
00:15:08,041 --> 00:15:09,625
[ANNOUNCER]
Now for the beanbag toss.

393
00:15:09,708 --> 00:15:11,291
[SAIKI]
If we're gonna turn it around,

394
00:15:11,375 --> 00:15:12,500
it's gotta be at this event--

395
00:15:12,583 --> 00:15:14,041
Our comeback starts now!

396
00:15:14,125 --> 00:15:16,250
[MALE ANNOUNCER] All the classes
are tossing bags.

397
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:18,833
There's a time limit.
Hold them all at once.

398
00:15:20,375 --> 00:15:22,083
You're not getting anywhere
near the hoop.

399
00:15:23,916 --> 00:15:26,125
[SAIKI] I'll stop the beanbags
right above the basket

400
00:15:26,208 --> 00:15:27,875
for a split-second
and drop them.

401
00:15:27,958 --> 00:15:30,291
He is still throwing them,
and the rulebook says nothing

402
00:15:30,375 --> 00:15:31,541
about using psychic powers.

403
00:15:31,625 --> 00:15:33,875
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
All right, that's time.

404
00:15:33,958 --> 00:15:36,416
Class One, 33 beanbags.
Class Two, 28.

405
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:37,958
[BOY]
We're still winning overall.

406
00:15:38,041 --> 00:15:39,583
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
Class Three...

407
00:15:39,666 --> 00:15:40,833
[ALL]
We tripled them!

408
00:15:40,916 --> 00:15:41,916
[SAIKI]
I might've overdone it.

409
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,541
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
Class Four has 100.

410
00:15:43,625 --> 00:15:46,916
It's not that difficult
if you use your head. Just look.

411
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,375
[HAIRO]
What the hell is that?

412
00:15:48,458 --> 00:15:50,166
[TANIHARA]
Well, what does it look like?

413
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:52,916
Everyone in Class Four put all
his bags in one larger bag.

414
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:55,458
That way, we threw a hundred
in the basket with one toss.

415
00:15:55,541 --> 00:15:58,791
[SAIKI] Wow. That's not smart,
that's just cheating.

416
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:01,083
Now, now, guys,
don't go using the C-word.

417
00:16:01,166 --> 00:16:03,375
The rules say nothing about
putting all your beanbags

418
00:16:03,458 --> 00:16:05,250
--in one big bag.
--[SAIKI] Well, they should.

419
00:16:05,333 --> 00:16:07,250
But there's still
one last event.

420
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:09,041
The inter-class relay race.

421
00:16:09,125 --> 00:16:11,708
And whichever team wins this one
will get a whopping 500 points

422
00:16:11,791 --> 00:16:13,333
added to their overall
total score.

423
00:16:13,416 --> 00:16:15,791
Saiki, I want you
running the anchor leg.

424
00:16:15,875 --> 00:16:18,208
[SAIKI] If I say no, things will
only get more difficult.

425
00:16:18,291 --> 00:16:20,666
I'll just finish third again,
like I did in the first race.

426
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:22,291
On your marks.
Set.

427
00:16:22,375 --> 00:16:24,208
--[starter pistol fires]
--[HAIRO] Go, Kaidou!

428
00:16:24,291 --> 00:16:25,833
[KAIDOU]
I am not gonna lose.

429
00:16:25,916 --> 00:16:28,333
[MALE ANNOUNCER] Class Three
has already fallen behind.

430
00:16:28,416 --> 00:16:29,875
They're the last
to pass...

431
00:16:29,958 --> 00:16:30,750
[KAIDOU]
I tried.

432
00:16:30,833 --> 00:16:32,125
[TAKAHASHI] Thanks for nothing.

433
00:16:32,208 --> 00:16:34,291
Looks like it's time for
Takahashi to take the lead.

434
00:16:34,375 --> 00:16:36,500
[MALE ANNOUNCER] And again,
Class Three's the last

435
00:16:36,583 --> 00:16:38,125
to pass the baton.

436
00:16:38,208 --> 00:16:40,458
But Nendou's unusual stride
is closing the gap.

437
00:16:40,541 --> 00:16:42,000
Class Three is winning the leg.

438
00:16:42,083 --> 00:16:44,541
[SAIKI] He's even creepier
at high speed.

439
00:16:44,625 --> 00:16:46,791
[MALE ANNOUNCER] Running
the next leg is Teruhashi,

440
00:16:46,875 --> 00:16:47,791
the running goddess.

441
00:16:47,875 --> 00:16:49,125
[TERUHASHI]
That's right, boys.

442
00:16:49,208 --> 00:16:50,541
I can run fast too.

443
00:16:50,625 --> 00:16:52,291
After all, I'm the perfect,
pretty girl.

444
00:16:52,375 --> 00:16:54,583
[NARRATOR] And so, Class Three
maintains their lead,

445
00:16:54,666 --> 00:16:56,333
finally passing the baton
to Hairo,

446
00:16:56,416 --> 00:16:58,083
their last runner
before Saiki.

447
00:16:58,166 --> 00:17:00,833
[HAIRO] Great work, guys.
Now to just get this to Saiki.

448
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:04,416
What are you doing?

449
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:05,875
Not a good time for this!

450
00:17:05,958 --> 00:17:07,625
[SAIKI] I knew he'd show it
at some point.

451
00:17:07,708 --> 00:17:09,916
At least it won't look
suspicious when I finish last.

452
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,666
We're totally gonna win now

453
00:17:11,750 --> 00:17:14,083
Nothing wrong with tripping
someone, if no one sees you.

454
00:17:14,166 --> 00:17:16,000
[SAIKI] Well, now that
changes everything.

455
00:17:16,083 --> 00:17:17,291
You should have kept quiet.

456
00:17:17,375 --> 00:17:19,041
Sorry! I fell!

457
00:17:19,125 --> 00:17:21,375
[SAIKI]
It's not your fault, it's his.

458
00:17:21,458 --> 00:17:22,333
[all gasp]

459
00:17:25,166 --> 00:17:26,916
--Payback time.
--[BOY 1] What the heck?

460
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,083
[BOY 2] This guy's flying.

461
00:17:28,166 --> 00:17:29,125
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
Class Three has once again

462
00:17:29,208 --> 00:17:30,875
come back from
last place to first.

463
00:17:30,958 --> 00:17:32,000
[SAIKI] I hate the attention,
but this way,

464
00:17:32,083 --> 00:17:37,708
I at least avoid
getting a buzz cut-- Uh!

465
00:17:37,791 --> 00:17:40,541
[SAIKI] Oh, right. I'm having
trouble controlling my body.

466
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,958
[NARRATOR]
And so, the next morning.

467
00:17:44,041 --> 00:17:46,500
[SAIKI] My name is Kusuo Saiki.
I have psychic superpowers.

468
00:17:46,583 --> 00:17:48,458
--Looking good, buddy.
--[SAIKI] Shut up, Hairo.

469
00:17:48,541 --> 00:17:50,833
--[KAIDOU] Hey, Saiki...
--[SAIKI] Boy, you went all out.

470
00:17:50,916 --> 00:17:53,583
What's going on with your hair?
It looks so weird.

471
00:17:53,666 --> 00:17:54,875
[SAIKI]
We have the same cut.

472
00:17:54,958 --> 00:17:56,791
[HAIRO] What's up?
Where are your buzz cuts?

473
00:17:56,875 --> 00:17:58,541
We only had to do it
if we lost to Class Two,

474
00:17:58,625 --> 00:17:59,625
and we beat them, right?

475
00:17:59,708 --> 00:18:02,000
[ALL]
Oh, wow.

476
00:18:02,083 --> 00:18:06,625
[man singing in Japanese]

477
00:18:07,583 --> 00:18:11,041
♪

478
00:18:12,416 --> 00:18:14,083
[HAIRO]
All right, everyone, listen up.

479
00:18:14,166 --> 00:18:15,541
Today we're doing
a safety drill.

480
00:18:15,625 --> 00:18:17,041
[SAIKI]
Safety drill? Okay.

481
00:18:17,125 --> 00:18:18,875
I don't need a drill.
I'll be fine.

482
00:18:18,958 --> 00:18:21,041
Nendou, you need
to take this seriously.

483
00:18:21,125 --> 00:18:22,875
Imagine this room's on fire.

484
00:18:22,958 --> 00:18:24,625
White-hot flames
are everywhere.

485
00:18:24,708 --> 00:18:27,750
The smoke makes it impossible
to see, let alone breathe.

486
00:18:27,833 --> 00:18:30,333
So what then?
You got an escape plan?

487
00:18:30,416 --> 00:18:32,166
How will you know
what decision to make

488
00:18:32,250 --> 00:18:33,916
if you don't participate
in this drill?

489
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,958
Preparation is the key
to survival!

490
00:18:36,041 --> 00:18:38,375
[SAIKI] You're as hot
and smothering as a fire.

491
00:18:38,458 --> 00:18:40,541
So when the alarm goes off,
follow my lead

492
00:18:40,625 --> 00:18:43,333
and evacuate to the courtyard.
[ALL] Okay.

493
00:18:43,416 --> 00:18:45,000
[HAIRO] Here's an easy
way to remember

494
00:18:45,083 --> 00:18:46,750
the correct procedure
in any emergency.

495
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:48,750
What's "SOS"?
[SAIKI] If I remember correctly

496
00:18:48,833 --> 00:18:51,416
from grade school, it means
"Slow," "Orderly," and "Silent."

497
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:52,583
I know what that stands for.

498
00:18:52,666 --> 00:18:54,375
"Save Our Selves." SOS.

499
00:18:54,458 --> 00:18:56,166
[SAIKI]
That's terrible.

500
00:18:56,250 --> 00:18:58,208
Yeah, that's the plan,
but it doesn't mean that.

501
00:18:58,291 --> 00:19:00,750
If it's not that, how about,
"Someone. Over here. Save Me."

502
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:02,541
[SAIKI]
You're on your own, pal.

503
00:19:02,625 --> 00:19:05,125
heh, heh. Each of your guesses
is dumber than the last one.

504
00:19:05,208 --> 00:19:07,541
[NENDOU] All right, do you know
what it means, smart guy?

505
00:19:07,625 --> 00:19:08,583
Of course I do.

506
00:19:08,666 --> 00:19:10,291
It stands for
"Scorching

507
00:19:10,375 --> 00:19:12,666
Oblivion
Smackdown."

508
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:14,333
Hey, I'm joking.

509
00:19:14,416 --> 00:19:16,666
It stands for "Slow,"
"Orderly," and "Silent," right?

510
00:19:16,750 --> 00:19:18,208
Yeah, you got it.

511
00:19:18,291 --> 00:19:20,250
Now, everyone just remember
those simple rules

512
00:19:20,333 --> 00:19:22,166
and we'll ace this drill.
[alarm bell rings]

513
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:24,583
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER] First-floor
science lab is on fire.

514
00:19:24,666 --> 00:19:26,125
That alarm always makes me
nervous.

515
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:28,041
[SAIKI]
We should pay attention.

516
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:29,458
Stay calm, everyone.

517
00:19:29,541 --> 00:19:31,166
Open your bag and get
your safety hoods.

518
00:19:31,250 --> 00:19:32,333
Stand in line
after that

519
00:19:32,416 --> 00:19:33,791
in order of
student number.

520
00:19:33,875 --> 00:19:35,875
[BOY 1] Where's my hood?
[BOY 2] Is this it?

521
00:19:35,958 --> 00:19:38,166
Oh, crap. I'm pretty sure
I left my hood at home.

522
00:19:38,250 --> 00:19:40,541
Seriously? If this was
an actual fire,

523
00:19:40,625 --> 00:19:42,541
obviously you'd be
smoldering ashes!

524
00:19:42,625 --> 00:19:44,000
[SAIKI] Don't be dramatic.

525
00:19:44,083 --> 00:19:45,583
I can't find
my safety hood, either.

526
00:19:45,666 --> 00:19:47,541
What? Oh, come on,
not you too.

527
00:19:47,625 --> 00:19:48,958
Use my hood, Teruhashi.

528
00:19:49,041 --> 00:19:51,375
If I take all of yours,
then you'll die.

529
00:19:51,458 --> 00:19:53,375
She's right.
This is not a safe plan.

530
00:19:53,458 --> 00:19:55,041
Sacrifice...

531
00:19:55,125 --> 00:19:56,208
Ourselves
to...

532
00:19:56,291 --> 00:19:57,208
Save her.

533
00:19:57,291 --> 00:19:58,833
Oh. Okay.

534
00:19:58,916 --> 00:20:01,166
[TERUHASHI] Saying nary a word.
Offering theirs to me.

535
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:02,291
Slaves of love.

536
00:20:02,375 --> 00:20:03,583
[HAIRO]
Okay, let's move out.

537
00:20:03,666 --> 00:20:05,291
Hold on.
I forgot my phone.

538
00:20:05,375 --> 00:20:07,125
Stop, Takahashi.
Out of line

539
00:20:07,208 --> 00:20:08,625
is too dangerous.
Stay in place.

540
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:10,500
[SAIKI]
Everyone's trying way too hard

541
00:20:10,583 --> 00:20:13,125
with these SOS abbreviations
now. It's all I'm hearing.

542
00:20:13,208 --> 00:20:16,250
Stop it, guys. Obviously, it's
not the time for stupid fights.

543
00:20:16,333 --> 00:20:18,208
[SAIKI]
See? They're everywhere.

544
00:20:18,291 --> 00:20:19,208
[gasps]

545
00:20:19,291 --> 00:20:21,000
Chiyo, hi.

546
00:20:21,083 --> 00:20:22,583
Hey, wait.

547
00:20:22,666 --> 00:20:24,833
[YUMEHARA] Splitting up with
a guy in the same school

548
00:20:24,916 --> 00:20:26,500
is overwhelmingly awkward
and tough.

549
00:20:26,583 --> 00:20:28,500
[SAIKI] This doesn't have
to do with the drill.

550
00:20:28,583 --> 00:20:29,750
[TAKERU]
The ex-girlfriend

551
00:20:29,833 --> 00:20:30,833
I can't forget.

552
00:20:30,916 --> 00:20:32,291
She's oblivious
to my suffering.

553
00:20:32,375 --> 00:20:33,625
[SAIKI] Why are
you doing this?

554
00:20:33,708 --> 00:20:35,333
[HAIRO]
Okay, gang, we're almost out.

555
00:20:35,416 --> 00:20:37,875
Stop! Stop, everyone!

556
00:20:37,958 --> 00:20:39,125
Our path
leading out,

557
00:20:39,208 --> 00:20:40,541
shuttered before us!

558
00:20:40,625 --> 00:20:42,333
[BOY 1] Seriously?
[GIRL 1] Oh, come on.

559
00:20:42,416 --> 00:20:43,875
[BOY 2]
Screw it, we'd be dead.

560
00:20:43,958 --> 00:20:44,916
[NENDOU]
That's weird.

561
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,333
Now we're completely trapped.

562
00:20:46,416 --> 00:20:48,000
I guess someone closed it
by mistake.

563
00:20:48,083 --> 00:20:50,875
[SAIKI] No. This route has been
closed with good reason.

564
00:20:50,958 --> 00:20:53,166
The science room
is directly in our path.

565
00:20:53,250 --> 00:20:55,875
Remember the intercom
announcement from earlier?

566
00:20:55,958 --> 00:20:58,291
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER] First-floor
science lab is on fire.

567
00:20:58,375 --> 00:21:00,041
[SAIKI] In this drill,
the lab is on fire.

568
00:21:00,125 --> 00:21:02,375
If this was real life,
the hallway would be impassable.

569
00:21:02,458 --> 00:21:04,458
They're testing to see
how well we paid attention

570
00:21:04,541 --> 00:21:05,916
and if we made the safer choice

571
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:07,916
of going down the back stairs,
which we didn't.

572
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:11,083
Stay calm. Obviously, there's
a solution to get outside.

573
00:21:11,166 --> 00:21:14,291
Yes, that's it. I understand
why they locked us in.

574
00:21:14,375 --> 00:21:17,291
[SAIKI]
Well, better late than never.

575
00:21:17,375 --> 00:21:19,083
They're testing
our physical strength.

576
00:21:19,166 --> 00:21:20,791
Yeah, that's the only
explanation.

577
00:21:20,875 --> 00:21:22,250
We don't have
to send out an SOS

578
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:23,541
if we can overcome obstacles

579
00:21:23,625 --> 00:21:24,541
by ourselves.

580
00:21:24,625 --> 00:21:25,541
Which means to get out,

581
00:21:25,625 --> 00:21:27,000
we must break down that shutter.

582
00:21:27,083 --> 00:21:28,750
[SAIKI] This is a fire drill,
not a movie.

583
00:21:28,833 --> 00:21:31,083
All right!
Let's break it down, boys!

584
00:21:31,166 --> 00:21:32,416
[yells]

585
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:33,583
Bash it with whatever!

586
00:21:33,666 --> 00:21:34,666
[SAIKI] In a real fire,

587
00:21:34,750 --> 00:21:36,166
they'd be the first to die.

588
00:21:36,250 --> 00:21:37,833
[MATSUZAKI]
So you wrenched open

589
00:21:37,916 --> 00:21:40,041
a metal shutter and ran out
the front door?

590
00:21:40,125 --> 00:21:42,791
I see. Why would you animals
break our new shutter?

591
00:21:42,875 --> 00:21:44,916
We literally installed it
last week, losers!

592
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:46,000
What are you
gonna do?

593
00:21:46,083 --> 00:21:47,166
Obviously
you're idiots!

594
00:21:47,250 --> 00:21:48,791
Shutters are
expensive to fix!

595
00:21:48,875 --> 00:21:50,375
[SAIKI]
I tried to warn them.

596
00:21:50,458 --> 00:21:51,916
Well, not directly, but still.

597
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:54,125
Anyway, this school doesn't
actually even need

598
00:21:54,208 --> 00:21:55,708
to bother with
emergency drills.

599
00:21:55,791 --> 00:21:57,541
After all...

600
00:21:57,625 --> 00:22:00,291
[MAN]
Life sucks.

601
00:22:00,375 --> 00:22:04,250
♪

602
00:22:04,333 --> 00:22:05,583
[fingers snap]

603
00:22:05,666 --> 00:22:07,875
[SAIKI]
So long as I'm here,

604
00:22:07,958 --> 00:22:10,000
ordeals like fires
simply won't happen.

605
00:22:10,083 --> 00:22:11,250
[MATSUZAKI]
As punishment,

606
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:12,916
you're all getting
buzz cuts.

607
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:17,000
♪

608
00:22:21,666 --> 00:22:23,458
[woman singing in Japanese]

609
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,375
[SAIKI]
You might not realize it,

610
00:23:43,458 --> 00:23:45,291
but I've been talking
this whole time.

611
00:23:45,375 --> 00:23:47,875
I actually just send my words
directly into people's brains.

612
00:23:47,958 --> 00:23:50,791
The end result is the same
as normal communication.

613
00:23:50,875 --> 00:23:53,583
Next time, in
<i>The Disastrous Life of Saiki K,</i>

614
00:23:53,666 --> 00:23:55,875
a 3000 yen coffee jelly?

